{
  "text": "The authors did not find any research studies on the relationship between the majority of PC (with the exception of the attitude of customers towards advertising -variable Personality 7) and CS, which means that either no research exists or that the relationship between these types of variables has not been proven. For an example of the latter, no relationship was shown between the level of optimism and CS concerning one product in the automotive and footwear industries [CITATION_1] . Our research showed no relationship between certain PC and CS.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "145054763"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "145054763": {
      "title": "Intrapersonal affective influences on consumer satisfaction with products",
      "abstract": "Research on consumer satisfaction with products has typically ignored influences other than the confirmation of expectations relative to product outcomes. This paper examines the impact of broader, intrapersonal affective variables on satisfaction, and presents empirical results on the relative effects of both types of influence."
    }
  }
}